==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adonai
<hw>Ad`o*na"i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>ad⟦omac⟧n⟦amac⟧i</ets>, lit., my lord.]</ety> <def>A Hebrew name
for God, usually translated in the Old Testament by the word
⟦ldquo⟧Lord⟦rdquo⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The later Jews used its vowel points to fill out the
tetragrammaton <er>Yhvh</er>, or <er>Ihvh</er>, ⟦ldquo⟧the
incommunicable name,⟦rdquo⟧ and in reading substituted
⟦ldquo⟧Adonai⟦rdquo⟧.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adonean</ent>⟦br⟧
